description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic pharmacist to join the Pain Services team of the Hywel Dda University Health Board Medicines Optimisation Team. This team currently consists of two pharmacists and two pharmacy technicians, who work closely with the multidisciplinary HDUHB Chronic Pain Service to help patients better manage their chronic pain. You will be responsible for reviewing and optimising the medication of patients who have been referred in to the Chronic Pain Service. This role can be very rewarding, giving you the opportunity to develop a relationship with patients, supporting them through a journey to enable them to live better with chronic pain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be responsible for supporting and advising GP Practices to review patients with chronic pain with the aim of reducing risk, improving quality and promoting cost effective and prudent prescribing. Education and learning is another key element for the team and you will be expected to deliver training sessions to GPs, pharmacists, pharmacy technicians and other health care professionals when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to demonstrate excellent clinical and communication skills, have a confident professional manner and be keen to learn and develop your expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although experience in Primary Care or Pain Management is not essential, possessing the enthusiasm to work autonomously across both primary and secondary care is essential as is the desire to develop in an evolving field. You will work closely with a pharmacy technician and the Medicines Optimisation Team will provide support when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be based in the Primary Care office in Haverfordwest but you will work across the Health Board and the ability to travel between sites in a timely manner is essential. The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job share or part time working will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews for this post will be held on 3rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRob BevanJob titleLead Pharmacist for Pain Services.Email addressrobert.bevan2@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01554 783281Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
